  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      During the stand phase the DMD foot is too plantarflexed in addition patients adopt a higher
      flexion and abduction of the hip in order to advance the swinging limb. The aim of this work
      is to assess the immediate contribution of heels for these walking disturbance in children
      with muscular dystrophy disease.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
